This file is intentionally not an applyable upstream patch.

Historical name:
  0001-metal-fuse-fp8-scaled-matmul-scheduler.patch

Status:
  Retired local artifact. Keep the filename so existing docs and probe commands
  still resolve, but do not run `git apply` on this file.

Why retired:
  The previous version was a bogus patch-B story: it rewrote
  the per-element FP8 product into a scaled-operands multiply. That is only
  algebraic reassociation. It is not scale-after-dot, not a packed uint32/LUT
  dot4 Metal hot loop, not a 4-way K unroll, and not an M == 1 simd_sum vecmat
  specialization.

Current honest Path C story:
  The local cppmega.mlx MLX/Metal Path C reference is
  `cppmega_mlx/nn/_tilelang/fp8_vecmat_path_c.py`. Its dispatchable runtime
  body uses packed `uint32` loads, `fp8_e4m3fn_lut` dot4 decode, a 4-byte K
  stride, `simd_sum(sum)`, and applies scales after the accumulated dot:
  `C[row] = sum * sx * sw`.

Upstream status:
  There is no accepted upstream TileLang tileop scheduler for this operation
  in this artifact. A real upstream patch would need to add scheduler/codegen
  support that preserves scale-after-dot and emits the packed Metal hot loop
  shape above. This file makes no CUDA/H200 acceptance claim.
